description.narrative: Output 5 (Nutrition in emergencies): Governments and partners at national and sub-national level have increasing evidence to address the impact of climate change on nutrition and improved capacity to prepare for, respond to, and recover from disasters in a timely and coordinated manner to ensure the nutrition status of the population including the most vulnerable groups is protected, which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Pregnant and lactating mothers, children aged under 5 years, and adolescents, including the most vulnerable groups utilize quality and equitable essential nutrition services and adopt appropriate diet and care practices
